13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 803 of Title 17, unless there is
16 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 A. Not later than ninety (90) days after the effective date of
18 this act, the Corporation Commission shall start the process to
19 engage an outside consulting firm to conduct a technical and legal
20 feasibility study on nuclear energy generation in this state. This
21 engagement shall be exempt from the state procurement process under
22 Section 85.1 et seq. of Title 74 of the Oklahoma Statutes and follow
23 the Corporation Commission process to retain expert witnesses on
24 behalf of the agency to ensure the ability to timely conduct the
