1 stud y and complete the requirements of this section. The consulting
2 firm shall be well-established in the nuclear industry.
3 B. The feasibility study shall evaluate and consider:
4 1. Advantages and disadvantages of generating nuclear energy in
5 this state, including, but not limited to, the economic and
6 environmental impacts;
7 2. Methods to maximize existing workforce and products made in
8 this state for the construction of nuclear energy generation
9 facilities;
10 3. Design characteristics, including recommendations for design
11 specification and site selection;
12 4. Environmental and ecological impacts;
13 5. Land and siting criteria, including specific geographic
14 areas that are best suited for new nuclear generation, as well as
15 cities near military bases that may use new nuclear electric
16 generation to meet the military resiliency requirements of 10
17 U.S.C., Section 2920;
18 6. Safety criteria;
19 7. Engineering and cost-related information;
20 8. Small modular nuclear reactor and microreactors capability;
21 and
22 9. Socioeconomic factors, including, but not limited to:
23 a. workforce education, training, and development,
24 b. local and state tax base,
